Introduction
Z4, LLC provides games and related services
under the brand name HD Poker (“HD Poker” or “us”
or “we”), including our social or “free-to-play”
games and related services that are presented on social networking
websites, such as
www.Facebook.com
(collectively,
the “Services”).
Your privacy is very important to Z4. This
Privacy Policy is designed to explain to you what information Z4
collects and how the information is used. By using the Services, you
agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy as updated from time to
time. We may update the terms of the Privacy Policy at any time for
any reason and will provide you with thirty (30) days written notice
of these changes either through email or through a notice provided by
the Services. Your continued use of the Services after the update
means that you agree to the changes to the Privacy Policy.
If you are located in California, please see
our Privacy Notice for California Consumers appended to this Privacy
Policy.
Information We Collect
To provide the best experience for our users
and to comply with applicable regulations and laws, Z4 collects a
variety of information relating to your use of the Services. We’ll
collect some information from other companies, including social
networks, if you access our games through your accounts with those
companies or you choose to connect your accounts with companies to
our Services.  The types of information collected by Z4 are
categorized into Personally Identifiable Information and
Non-Personally Identifiable Information. Together, this information
is referred to as “Collected Information.” When you
create an account for the Services, Z4 collects the following
Personally Identifiable Information:
First and Last Name
Your user identification number (like Facebook
	ID number), which may be linked to publicly-available information
	like your name and profile photo;
Email Address
Friends list
Your gender
Your birthday, age, and/or age range
Information about your activities on or
	through the connected third-party application;
Other publicly available information on the
	third-party application
Anh other information that you or the provider
	of the third-party application share with Z4.
If you access our Services from a third-party
application or connect our Services to a third-party application, you
should also read that third-party application’s terms of
service and privacy policy.
If you are unclear about what information a
third-party application is sharing with us, please go to the
third-party application to find out more about their privacy
practices.
If you choose to purchase in-game currency or
other in-game content, Z4’s third-party payment processors will
collect the billing and financial information they need to process
your order. This may include your email, your address, and other
necessary financial information. Z4’s payment processors do not
share your financial information like credit card numbers, but they
may share non-financial information with Z4 related to your order,
such as your name, billing address, and the items purchased.
When you use the Services on connected
third-party platforms like Facebook, Apple iOS. Steam (Valve), or
Google Android, these purchases are services by the respective
platform and are subject to the individual third-party application’s
terms of service and privacy policy.
When you use the Services on poker.hd.io, you
are subject to HD Poker’s third-party processor. For details on
how these purchases are served, go
to:
https://www.braintreepayments.com/legal
In addition, Z4 may automatically collect
Non-Personally Identifiable Information, such as how you interact
with the Services, your IP address, and the URL of a website that
referred you to the Services, if applicable. As part of this effort,
Z4 may temporarily store cookies on the device you use to access the
Services. Z4 may also assign an anonymized identification number to
your account that may be used for analyzing how you and other players
interact with the Services, advertisements, and referring websites.
How we use the Collected Information
We will use the Collected Information to ensure
compliance with applicable laws and regulations in the jurisdictions
that we operate in.
From time to time, we may send emails to you to
notify you of events, promotions, and other information we believe
will be of interest to you. You may opt out of these emails by
following the directions listed in the email, or by emailing your
request to
support@z4.com
.
Information we share with third parties
Your Member name, chat contributions and forum
posts will be visible to other users of the Services when you use the
Services.
We do not sell or rent your Personally
Identifiable Information to third parties. However, we may send
Non-Personally Identifiable Information to third parties to enable
advertisements to appear within the Services and to enable affiliate
marketers to refer players to the Services. We may also share the
anonymized identifier with select partners to analyze how players
interact with the Services.
If you purchase goods or services related to
the Services, we will share your Personally Identifiable Information
with banks, credit card companies, or other payment processors as
needed to complete your purchase. These third parties are ordinarily
located in the USA.
We may also share Collected Information with
law enforcement personnel, regulatory agencies, or other personnel to
comply with subpoenas, search warrants, court orders, gaming
regulations, or other laws or regulations that we believe require us
to disclose the information. In addition, we may share Collected
Information to preserve our rights or property, to preserve the
rights or property of our affiliates, and to investigate or prevent
the commission of a crime.
Your Personally Identifiable Information will
be stored on encrypted servers and computers located in the USA where
data protection and privacy regulations may differ from those in
other parts of the world.
Policy towards minors
The Services are intended only to be used by
persons eighteen (18) years of age or older. We never intend to
collect information from minors (those persons under the age of 18).
If we find out that we have inadvertently collected Personally
Identifiable Information of a minor, we will delete the information
from our systems.
Third Party Links
Our Services may contain links to websites
operated and maintained by third parties over which we have
absolutely no control. These third-party websites are not subject to
this Privacy Policy or our privacy standards and procedures. Any
information you provide to third party websites will be governed by
the terms of the websites’ privacy policies. We have no
responsibility or liability whatsoever for the content, actions or
policies of third-party websites. The inclusion of third-party links
in any of our Services in no way constitutes an endorsement of such
websites’ content, actions or policies.
Cookies
Z4 uses cookies. Cookies collect information
that includes the server your computer or device is logged onto, your
browser type and how you gained entry to our Services. Therefore,
when you access our Services, details are recorded about your visit,
such as time and date and pages accessed. As stated above, this
Non-Personally Identifiable Information is used in an anonymous form
for statistical purposes and, as such, cannot be used to identify you
individually. A cookie cannot retrieve any other information from
your hard drive, pass on computer viruses or capture your email
address or any other Personally Identifiable Information.
Check the “Help” menu of your
browser for more information on how to change your cookie
preferences. You may disable cookies or set your browser to alert you
when cookies are being sent. If you do disable cookies, we may be
unable to optimize your use of our Services and you may experience
some errors. Refer to your browser instructions or help screens to
learn about these functions.
Requests for access and correction of
Personally Identifiable Information
You are entitled to access and correct the
Personally Identifiable Information we hold about you and to have any
inaccuracies in the information corrected.
If you would like to access, update or correct
any of the Personally Identifiable Information we hold about you, you
may do so by contacting us using the Contact Details below and
informing us that you wish to access or correct your Personally
Identifiable Information.
There are some circumstances specified by law
where we may refuse your request for access to and/or the correction
of your Personally Identifiable Information. However, if one of these
circumstances applies, we will provide you with a written explanation
of the reasons for refusal, unless it would be unreasonable to
provide that notice.
Once we receive your request for access or
correction, we will endeavor to respond to your request within thirty
(30) days after the request is made. We may also charge reasonable
costs for responding to your request.
Complaints
If you have any concerns or a complaint about a
breach of your privacy or the way we have handled your Personally
Identifiable Information, please contact us using the Contact Details
below and inform us of the nature of your complaint.
We will then investigate your complaint and
endeavor to provide you with our response within thirty (30) days.
For Australian residents: If, after receiving
our response you still consider that your privacy complaint remains
unresolved, you may then, for example, refer your concern to the
Office of the Australian Information Commissioner at
www.oaic.gov.au
.
